subSection.paragraph:
Compounds 24 , 25 , 27 , 28b , and 30 were assigned to lutein esters according to their retention times as well as UV/vis and MS data compared to reference compounds obtained from marigold (
Tagetes sp.
) extract and literature data ( Rodrigues et al., 2019 ; Breithaupt et al., 2002). In the APCI() mode, molecular ions [M] • were detected at m/z 960 ( 25 ), m/z 988 ( 27 ), and m/z 1016 ( 30 ), matching with those of (all- E )-lutein laurate myristate, (all- E )-lutein dimyristate, and (all- E )--lutein myristate palmitate, respectively. In the APCI(+) mode, (all- E )--lutein dimyristate ( 27 ) revealed a single in-source fragment at m/z 761 ([M + H – 228] + ) owing to the spontaneous loss of myristic acid at the ε- ring. By contrast, lutein heterodiesters ( 25 , 30 ) revealed two distinct in-source fragments each, being detected at m/z 733 ([M + H – 228] + ) and m/z 761 ([M + H – 200] + ) for (all- E )-lutein laurate myristate ( 25 ) and m/z 761 ([M + H – 256] + ) and m/z 789 ([M + H – 228] + ) for (all- E )-lutein myristate palmitate ( 30 ) in accordance with the literature ( Wen et al., 2017 ; Rodrigues et al., 2019 ; Breithaupt et al., 2002). Co-elution of regioisomers of lutein heterodiesters presumably hindered their differentiation in our chromatogram compared to a previous report of Rodrigues et al. (2019) . In the APCI(+)-MS 2 experiment, characteristic product ions were detected at m/z 533, 441, and 411, further substantiating the assignment of all compounds to lutein esters ( 24 , 25 , 27 , 28b , 30 ). Moreover, UV/vis spectra (sh424, 446, and 474 nm ) resembled that of (all- E )-lutein ( 2 ), except for the absorption signal of compound 28b being overlaid by the unresolved eschscholtzxanthin myristate ( 28a ).

